      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHARMING SEAHORSE (2) was well supported on debut and showed pace before fading for third over 1100m at Mackay. Likely improver with leading rider going on. Take catching. DIANTE (5) is a two-start maiden who looks close to a win after placing at both runs, the latest when second over 1100m at Mackay. Has the pace to settle in the leading division. Likely to feature. ASTILLA (6) is an interesting one to line up. Made debut at Caulfield then went for a spell and switched yards. Showed pace in her first run in this area before veering to the outside rail, taking control of the rider and dropping right out. Has since won a trial. Well worth another chance. AIRBORNE AFFAIR (1) is a colt by Trapeze Artist from She's My Girl on debut. Won a recent Beaudesert trial. Showing ability at the trials and expected to run well. HOPE SO (7) is a two-year-old filly making her debut by The Odyssey out of Roux Star. Won a trial here and worth keeping safe.",
